The paper deals with the extraction and simulation of secret correlations, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of common information and protocols also suggests a connection to communication complexity (cs.CC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the mention of local operations and public communication may indicate a link to quantum information and computation (cs.SI).
